-- Schlecker’s Logistics Provider Made Profits, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-06-04T16:58:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-04/schlecker-s-logistics-provider-made-profits-handelsblatt-says.html
German retail chain Schlecker’s LDG
logistics provider, which belonged to the children of its
founder Anton Schlecker, had profit margins of 27.5 percent in
the past few years while its only client Schlecker made losses,
 Handelsblatt  reported in a preview of an article that will be
published tomorrow, without saying where it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
